Quickstrike:




He should of expected an outburst like this from her. When he usually 
would have ducked and sucked up to her, Quickstrike laughed, 
quivering the metal strips at his cheeks.

"Sugar-bot," he said, after his laugh. "Primus...Ya got yerself an 
imagination." He grinned. "There ain't never gonna be uh way ah 
b'tray ya. Yer th' prettiest and smartest thing on this planet." He 
shook his head. "Ah met up wit' this horse-bot, Wildfire. She's uh 
pshyic. So, ah got uh upper hand. Ah learned how t' do it wit' her. 
Dang scarry at first, but ah'm gettin' th' hang of it." He looked at 
Blackarachnia. "Ah know ya can handle yerself. Now, ah'm gonna be 
back, ah promise. Cross mah spark." He crossed his arms. "That kid 
oughta be able t' handle herself, every Pred's gotta. Ah did ah you 
did. She's got th' weapons and brains, huh? Jus' gotta be pacient."

Wildfire appeared at the corner of his optics, stepping slowly, and 
stepped within three steps. The image of Blackarachnia and 
Quickstrike together went through the air with the help of the horse. 

Quickstrike stared Blackarachnia down.
